Part 3 — Configure DI in Program.cs

Add (or update) service registrations and lifetimes:

// IClient registered as Singleton (reuse across the app lifecycle)
builder.Services.AddSingleton<IClient>(sp =>
{
    string key = builder.Configuration["OpenWeather:Key"];
    return new Client(key, new HttpClient());
});

// INowWrapper registered as Singleton (thread-safe and stateless)
builder.Services.AddSingleton<INowWrapper, NowWrapper>();

// IRandomWrapper registered as Transient (avoid shared mutable state)
builder.Services.AddTransient<IRandomWrapper, RandomWrapper>();

In your summary, briefly justify why each lifetime was chosen.
